Task 1: Extract MFT Data Using MFTECmd
Subtask 1.1: Install Required Tools
Install MFTECmd and dependencies:

# Update system packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install .NET runtime for MFTECmd
wget https://packages.microsoft.com/config/ubuntu/20.04/packages-microsoft-prod.deb -O packages-microsoft-prod.deb
sudo dpkg -i packages-microsoft-prod.deb
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y dotnet-runtime-6.0

# Download MFTECmd
wget https://download.sysinternals.com/files/MFTECmd.zip
sudo apt install -y unzip
unzip MFTECmd.zip -d /opt/MFTECmd/
sudo chmod +x /opt/MFTECmd/MFTECmd.exe
Subtask 1.2: Create Sample NTFS Image
Create a sample NTFS filesystem for analysis:

# Create a sample disk image
dd if=/dev/zero of=sample_ntfs.img bs=1M count=100

# Format as NTFS
sudo apt install -y ntfs-3g
sudo mkfs.ntfs -f sample_ntfs.img

# Mount the image
mkdir /tmp/ntfs_mount
sudo mount -o loop sample_ntfs.img /tmp/ntfs_mount

# Create sample files with different timestamps
sudo touch /tmp/ntfs_mount/file1.txt
sudo touch /tmp/ntfs_mount/file2.doc
echo "Sample content" | sudo tee /tmp/ntfs_mount/document.txt
sudo mkdir /tmp/ntfs_mount/folder1

# Unmount to preserve MFT
sudo umount /tmp/ntfs_mount
Subtask 1.3: Extract MFT from Image
Extract the MFT using dd command:

# Calculate MFT location (typically starts at sector 786432 for small volumes)
# For this lab, we'll extract the first few MB which contains MFT
dd if=sample_ntfs.img of=extracted_mft.bin bs=512 skip=0 count=2048

# Verify MFT signature
hexdump -C extracted_mft.bin | head -5
Task 2: Analyze File Records and Timestamps in MFT
Subtask 2.1: Parse MFT with MFTECmd
Run MFTECmd to parse the extracted MFT:

# Parse MFT and output to CSV
dotnet /opt/MFTECmd/MFTECmd.exe -f extracted_mft.bin --csv /tmp/mft_output --csvf mft_analysis.csv

# Alternative: Parse with detailed output
dotnet /opt/MFTECmd/MFTECmd.exe -f extracted_mft.bin --csv /tmp/mft_output --csvf detailed_mft.csv -v
Subtask 2.2: Analyze MFT Records
Examine the parsed MFT data:

# View CSV headers
head -1 /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv

# Count total records
wc -l /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv

# View first 10 file records
head -10 /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv | column -t -s ','
Subtask 2.3: Extract Timestamp Information
Analyze timestamps and file metadata:

# Install CSV analysis tools
sudo apt install -y csvkit

# Extract files with specific extensions
csvgrep -c "Extension" -m ".txt" /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv

# Sort by creation time
csvsort -c "Created0x10" /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv | head -10

# Find deleted files (if any)
csvgrep -c "InUse" -m "False" /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv
Subtask 2.4: Generate Analysis Report
Create a summary report of findings:

# Create analysis script
cat > mft_analysis.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash
echo "=== MFT Analysis Report ==="
echo "Total MFT Records: $(wc -l < /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv)"
echo ""
echo "File Extensions Found:"
csvcut -c "Extension" /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv | sort | uniq -c | sort -nr
echo ""
echo "Files by Size (Top 5):"
csvsort -c "LogicalSize" -r /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv | head -6 | csvcut -c "FileName,LogicalSize"
echo ""
echo "Recently Created Files:"
csvsort -c "Created0x10" -r /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv | head -6 | csvcut -c "FileName,Created0x10"
EOF

chmod +x mft_analysis.sh
./mft_analysis.sh
Subtask 2.5: Examine Specific MFT Attributes
Analyze specific MFT attributes and metadata:

# Look for files with multiple data streams
csvgrep -c "HasAds" -m "True" /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv

# Find system files
csvgrep -c "FileName" -r "^\$" /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv | csvcut -c "FileName,EntryNumber"

# Check for resident vs non-resident files
csvstat -c "IsResident" /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv
Verification and Testing
Verify your analysis results:

# Validate CSV structure
csvclean /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv

# Generate statistics
csvstat /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv

# Create timeline of file activities
csvsort -c "Created0x10" /tmp/mft_output/mft_analysis.csv | csvcut -c "FileName,Created0x10,Modified0x10" > timeline.csv
head -10 timeline.csv
Common Issues and Troubleshooting
MFTECmd not executing: Ensure .NET runtime is properly installed and MFTECmd has execute permissions.

Empty CSV output: Verify the MFT file contains valid NTFS data using hexdump.

Permission errors: Use sudo when accessing raw disk images or system files.

Conclusion
You have successfully extracted and analyzed NTFS Master File Table data using MFTECmd. This lab demonstrated how to parse MFT records, extract file metadata, analyze timestamps, and generate forensic reports. Understanding MFT analysis is crucial for digital forensics investigations as it provides detailed information about file system activities, including deleted files, file creation patterns, and system metadata that may not be visible through normal file system access.

The skills learned in this lab are essential for forensic analysts investigating file system artifacts and understanding the complete picture of file system activities on NTFS volumes.
